1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:41,620 --> 00:01:46,170
Amigasa Village

3
00:01:42,210 --> 00:01:43,210
So...

4
00:01:43,210 --> 00:01:46,170
why were they after you?

5
00:01:46,170 --> 00:01:47,210
Huh?

6
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,760
Well...

7
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:56,680
I went into town to do some shopping...

8
00:01:56,680 --> 00:02:02,230
But on my way home, I ran into some of
the evil one's men and their baboon.

9
00:02:03,940 --> 00:02:08,520
To protect me, Komachiyo
attacked the baboon...

10
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:13,110
Ah, so that's why you guys were fighting.

11
00:02:15,990 --> 00:02:18,410
Meanwhile...

12
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:21,620
They stole what I had just bought!

13
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:26,500
Out of frustration,
I ended up saying something taboo.

14
00:02:32,090 --> 00:02:36,340
When the Kozuki Clan comes back,
they'll teach you a lesson!

15
00:02:37,010 --> 00:02:38,350
What was that?!

16
00:02:40,140 --> 00:02:41,560
Let me go!

17
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:52,780
I thought I'd never see my home again,

18
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:56,070
but thanks to you, I got away!

19
00:02:56,410 --> 00:02:59,950
So please let me return the favor!

20
00:02:59,950 --> 00:03:01,660
Oh! Sounds great!

21
00:03:01,660 --> 00:03:06,000
I just got here, so I have a lot of questions.

22
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:11,050
Okay then!

23
00:03:11,050 --> 00:03:13,260
You'll need food!

24
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,010
Is this okay?

25
00:03:19,010 --> 00:03:20,140
It is!

26
00:03:21,220 --> 00:03:24,230
No enemies can find it here.

27
00:03:25,890 --> 00:03:27,270
Damn!

28
00:03:27,270 --> 00:03:29,480
Looks like there's nothing left to eat!

29
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:30,900
Big Bro!

30
00:03:31,230 --> 00:03:33,110
Let's go now!

31
00:03:33,110 --> 00:03:34,190
Wh-What?

32
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:39,990
I'd like to invite you over for a treat!

33
00:03:42,450 --> 00:03:45,870
Big Bro! Hihimaru! This way!

34
00:03:42,580 --> 00:03:47,080
Komachiyo
A Lion-Dog

35
00:03:47,420 --> 00:03:50,590
Hihimaru
A New Friend

36
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:53,050
His name is Hihimaru?

37
00:03:53,050 --> 00:03:55,050
I just came up with it!

38
00:03:55,050 --> 00:03:56,550
I see.

39
00:03:56,550 --> 00:03:58,260
I'm counting on you, Hihimaru!

40
00:04:06,930 --> 00:04:12,190
So there are types of pirates that I like
and kinds I don't like!

41
00:04:12,980 --> 00:04:14,480
You can like who you want.

42
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:16,740
Huh?

43
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:23,530
You're the strong and kind type.

44
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:36,010
My house is over there.

45
00:04:38,050 --> 00:04:40,680
There's a village in the mountains?

46
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:43,050
No, not anymore!

47
00:04:43,390 --> 00:04:46,020
It's just my master and me now.

48
00:04:47,890 --> 00:04:52,690
I'm training to one day become...

49
00:04:53,610 --> 00:04:55,820
a bewitching kunoichi!

50
00:04:58,820 --> 00:05:00,280
"Bewitching"?

51
00:05:11,250 --> 00:05:13,500
It's dirty, small, and stinky here.

52
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:18,920
Big Bro, that's a little rude of you.

53
00:05:21,220 --> 00:05:23,720
Oh, that smells delicious!

54
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:26,100
It's almost done!

55
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:33,770
Is it ready yet, Tama?!

56
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:47,950
It's ready!

57
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:49,410
Here you go.

58
00:05:49,410 --> 00:05:53,000
Go ahead and dig in, Big Bro!

59
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:57,130
Freshly-cooked rice!

60
00:05:57,750 --> 00:05:59,760
Thank you for the meal!

61
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:10,100
It's delicious!

62
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:20,230
Aren't you gonna have any?

63
00:06:21,570 --> 00:06:23,360
No, not now.

64
00:06:24,950 --> 00:06:28,410
I can't become a ninja
if I'm not light on my feet!

65
00:06:33,370 --> 00:06:34,830
Seconds, please!

66
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:36,040
So quick!

67
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,840
But that was all I cooked.

68
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:41,760
What?

69
00:06:42,380 --> 00:06:44,970
We're out of pickles too...

70
00:06:44,970 --> 00:06:47,140
A-All right then.

71
00:06:48,010 --> 00:06:50,510
I was just joking when I asked for seconds.

72
00:06:56,650 --> 00:06:58,900
What?! You're bad at lying!

73
00:07:04,150 --> 00:07:07,110
I gotta go to the bathroom.

74
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:18,080
It wasn't enough, but it was
kind of her to cook for me.

75
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:21,170
She's a good kid, that Tama...

76
00:07:23,670 --> 00:07:26,510
Who the hell are you?!

77
00:07:28,550 --> 00:07:30,390
What?! Usopp...

78
00:07:31,350 --> 00:07:32,430
No, it's not!

79
00:07:34,310 --> 00:07:36,890
Why are you freeloading around here?!

80
00:07:44,820 --> 00:07:49,620
Don't tell me you ate the rice.

81
00:07:49,620 --> 00:07:51,240
I did.

82
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:51,950
Who are–

83
00:07:51,950 --> 00:07:55,750
You fool!

84
00:08:06,010 --> 00:08:07,800
Keep quiet, stomach!

85
00:08:08,380 --> 00:08:09,840
It's disgraceful!

86
00:08:16,310 --> 00:08:17,140
Wait!

87
00:08:17,730 --> 00:08:19,850
Wh-Who are you?!

88
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:23,770
I'm only here because Tama cooked for me.

89
00:08:24,980 --> 00:08:29,360
Why would Otama cook for you?

90
00:08:31,870 --> 00:08:36,370
How many days do you think it's been
since she last ate anything?!

91
00:08:36,370 --> 00:08:37,290
B-But...

92
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:42,670
Despite how hard she works everyday
to weave and sell hats,

93
00:08:42,670 --> 00:08:47,170
there is barely enough money
to sustain even a single person!

94
00:08:54,390 --> 00:08:58,350
Sometimes we eat barnyard grass,
and that's if we're lucky.

95
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:01,150
But at least, twice a year,

96
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:05,690
on her birthday and New Year's,
I want her to be able to eat rice!

97
00:09:05,820 --> 00:09:08,900
"Rice"

98
00:09:06,730 --> 00:09:08,900
So I sent her to town with some money

99
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:14,120
to buy some rice in celebration
of her eighth birthday!

100
00:09:19,620 --> 00:09:23,130
What lowlife would eat her rice?!

101
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,460
Master!

102
00:09:28,590 --> 00:09:30,170
Please stop!

103
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:35,430
Forgive me for cooking it without asking!

104
00:09:35,430 --> 00:09:37,010
But...

105
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:41,770
he saved my life!

106
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:45,520
Don't bring dishonor upon me!

107
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:48,320
I'll weave even more hats!

108
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:50,740
So please forgive me!

109
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:56,780
Just let me return the favor to
Big Bro Luffy properly...

110
00:09:57,330 --> 00:09:58,160
Please...

111
00:10:03,620 --> 00:10:04,790
Otama!

112
00:10:04,790 --> 00:10:05,710
Tama!

113
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:14,840
Hey, Tama!

114
00:10:17,140 --> 00:10:19,010
She's done something foolish!

115
00:10:19,010 --> 00:10:23,480
She drank the river water to ease her hunger.

116
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:24,400
Water?

117
00:10:27,110 --> 00:10:30,230
The river water in this country...

118
00:10:30,230 --> 00:10:35,870
is polluted by liquid waste
from Kaido's factories!

119
00:10:39,990 --> 00:10:45,750
For a small girl like her,
it's like drinking poison.

120
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:51,260
Then, why are you living here?!

121
00:10:53,420 --> 00:10:57,890
There are places that would be a bit better.

122
00:10:58,430 --> 00:11:01,600
But she's waiting here.

123
00:11:03,810 --> 00:11:06,900
For someone who promised to return...

124
00:11:09,230 --> 00:11:13,440
A pirate named Ace!

125
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:35,760
Tama...

126
00:11:40,140 --> 00:11:42,470
The Ace that you're waiting for...

127
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:47,350
is Portgas D. Ace, right?

128
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:52,520
Do you know him?

129
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:54,110
Big Bro...

130
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,200
Yeah.

131
00:12:06,750 --> 00:12:08,250
Ace is dead.

132
00:12:28,850 --> 00:12:30,230
That's a lie...

133
00:12:30,230 --> 00:12:31,480
That's a lie!

134
00:12:34,110 --> 00:12:36,780
That's a lie!

135
00:12:41,530 --> 00:12:44,790
Big Bro, you're a liar!

136
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:00,510
Tama!

137
00:13:00,510 --> 00:13:01,640
Otama!

138
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:03,300
Pull yourself together, Tama!

139
00:13:09,640 --> 00:13:11,480
She fainted.

140
00:13:14,020 --> 00:13:17,530
So Ace visited Wano too...

141
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:22,870
Are you a demon or something?!

142
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:27,490
How could you tell Otama
so casually that Ace died?

143
00:13:27,490 --> 00:13:29,370
But it's true.

144
00:13:29,370 --> 00:13:33,330
Even if it's true, that wasn't the right time!

145
00:13:33,330 --> 00:13:36,380
But no matter how long she waits,
Ace won't come back!

146
00:13:36,380 --> 00:13:38,090
But still...

147
00:13:38,420 --> 00:13:41,880
you should've considered
when and how to say it!

148
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:44,600
You clearly lack a sense of tact!

149
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:48,560
Who the hell are you anyway?!

150
00:13:49,060 --> 00:13:53,400
I'm Luffy, the man who's
gonna be King of the Pirates!

151
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:58,780
What?! You're a pirate?!

152
00:13:59,150 --> 00:14:01,280
I generally don't like pirates!

153
00:14:01,650 --> 00:14:03,660
Old guy, who are you?!

154
00:14:05,070 --> 00:14:06,740
I am Hitetsu.

155
00:14:06,950 --> 00:14:06,990
Tenguyama Hitetsu

Swordsmith

(And a Collector of Beautiful Kokeshi Dolls)

156
00:14:06,990 --> 00:14:07,030
Tenguyama Hitetsu

Swordsmith

(And a Collector of Beautiful Kokeshi Dolls)

157
00:14:07,030 --> 00:14:07,080
Tenguyama Hitetsu

Swordsmith

(And a Collector of Beautiful Kokeshi Dolls)

158
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:07,120
Tenguyama Hitetsu

Swordsmith

(And a Collector of Beautiful Kokeshi Dolls)

159
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:07,160
Tenguyama Hitetsu

Swordsmith

(And a Collector of Beautiful Kokeshi Dolls)

160
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:09,660
Tenguyama Hitetsu

Swordsmith

(And a Collector of Beautiful Kokeshi Dolls)

161
00:14:07,910 --> 00:14:09,660
I'm a swordsmith.

162
00:14:09,660 --> 00:14:12,870
Tenguyama Hitetsu

Swordsmith

(And a Collector of Beautiful Kokeshi Dolls)

163
00:14:13,210 --> 00:14:15,000
Ace is now gone!

164
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:18,750
Take Tama and move to a better place!

165
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:22,880
I truly want to do so.

166
00:14:23,510 --> 00:14:25,470
But, for some time now...

167
00:14:25,890 --> 00:14:29,520
I've been waiting for someone here myself.

168
00:14:31,850 --> 00:14:38,020
There are only the two of us here now,
but this was once Amigasa Village.

169
00:14:38,570 --> 00:14:41,070
Around a year ago...

170
00:14:41,070 --> 00:14:46,370
a new headliner joined
Kaido's army and came here.

171
00:14:48,830 --> 00:14:51,750
He was a pirate named X Drake.

172
00:14:58,380 --> 00:15:02,210
He defeated the five samurai
vital to the village...

173
00:15:02,210 --> 00:15:04,170
and everything was destroyed.

174
00:15:10,760 --> 00:15:16,020
Now, the only prosperous place in Wano...

175
00:15:16,020 --> 00:15:20,650
is the Flower Capital
where Shogun Orochi lives.

176
00:15:22,230 --> 00:15:24,030
Everywhere else...

177
00:15:24,030 --> 00:15:29,120
eventually became lawless wilderness
thanks to Kaido and his group.

178
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:36,080
It was four years ago when
that man came here.

179
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:41,040
This village was always poor...

180
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:47,220
and without enough to live on,
people often died of hunger.

181
00:15:47,930 --> 00:15:51,010
Just when we thought that
the village was doomed...

182
00:15:54,730 --> 00:15:57,600
Ace washed up on the beach.

183
00:15:59,690 --> 00:16:02,520
The villagers stole all the food and water...

184
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:06,900
from those helpless pirates.

185
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:10,660
They ate it all to survive.

186
00:16:18,210 --> 00:16:20,750
Ace watched them finish everything,

187
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:24,630
then, to everyone's surprise,
he easily untied himself.

188
00:16:26,510 --> 00:16:30,390
Everyone prepared for the retribution
they thought was coming.

189
00:16:38,020 --> 00:16:39,850
Did you have enough?

190
00:16:39,850 --> 00:16:41,100
What?

191
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:44,820
Uh... Uh-huh.

192
00:16:46,570 --> 00:16:49,660
Then it's time for something sweet!

193
00:16:50,070 --> 00:16:50,820
What?!

194
00:16:52,030 --> 00:16:54,740
Where can I find something for dessert?

195
00:16:55,660 --> 00:16:58,580
Alright, I'll bring it right back here!

196
00:16:58,580 --> 00:17:01,630
Everyone was stunned.

197
00:17:02,330 --> 00:17:06,760
Ace stayed at the village for several weeks.

198
00:17:08,670 --> 00:17:14,350
Otama was especially attached to him.

199
00:17:18,140 --> 00:17:23,770
I still can't believe shipwrecked
pirates saved our lives.

200
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:30,950
Yeah...

201
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:46,000
I see.

202
00:17:58,350 --> 00:17:59,270
Hey!

203
00:18:01,020 --> 00:18:03,400
Where can I get water and food?

204
00:18:08,530 --> 00:18:10,940
And is there a doctor around here?

205
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:12,990
Don't tell me...

206
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:15,870
I'm gonna take Tama...

207
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:18,240
in return for giving me food!

208
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:23,870
Wait, you fool!

209
00:18:24,250 --> 00:18:27,840
Your outlandish outfit is
too conspicuous! Put this on!

210
00:18:33,010 --> 00:18:35,640
Oh, it's a kimono!

211
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:37,140
Stay still!

212
00:18:37,140 --> 00:18:39,390
Samurai armor would be cool, too!

213
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:43,270
No one wears that every day!

214
00:18:45,520 --> 00:18:46,770
You're good to go!

215
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:52,530
There's a reason I can't go into town...

216
00:18:52,530 --> 00:18:54,200
so please take care of Otama!

217
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:57,700
I'll reimburse the doctor's fee later!

218
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:03,540
If I can meet my friends before that,
we'll get food and medical care for free!

219
00:19:03,540 --> 00:19:05,040
They'll help us!

220
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:15,220
Look what you got there!

221
00:19:19,470 --> 00:19:22,520
If I borrow this sword,
I'll look like a real samurai!

222
00:19:26,730 --> 00:19:28,190
Okay, see you!

223
00:19:28,610 --> 00:19:31,150
Tama! I'm taking you to a doctor now!

224
00:19:32,730 --> 00:19:33,900
No, wait!

225
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:36,030
You fool! You can't take that!

226
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:39,490
It's blasphemy to play around
with a famous sword!

227
00:19:39,490 --> 00:19:44,960
My ancestor, Kotetsu,
forged that world-famous sword!

228
00:19:45,460 --> 00:19:48,290
It's one of only twenty-one
great grade swords!

229
00:19:48,290 --> 00:19:51,920
It's called Kitetsu II!

230
00:19:53,130 --> 00:19:54,760
Listen!

231
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:57,380
Of the numerous swords in the world,

232
00:19:57,380 --> 00:20:01,720
great swordsmiths have created
what are known as grade swords.

233
00:20:03,810 --> 00:20:06,440
And the finest among them are called...

234
00:20:06,980 --> 00:20:09,310
the fifty fine grade swords,

235
00:20:09,310 --> 00:20:11,690
the twenty-one great grade swords,

236
00:20:11,690 --> 00:20:14,610
and the twelve supreme grade swords.

237
00:20:14,940 --> 00:20:18,860
There's a story behind Kitetsu in particular...

238
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:20,320
Huh?!

239
00:20:21,070 --> 00:20:21,830
He's gone!

240
00:20:28,670 --> 00:20:31,250
See you! I'm gonna take the sword!

241
00:20:31,250 --> 00:20:33,710
Hey! Listen to me!

242
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:37,340
Wait! Wait!

243
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:40,640
I said no!

244
00:20:41,390 --> 00:20:43,890
Then, let me borrow your sword instead!

245
00:20:43,890 --> 00:20:47,180
This is also a named blade!

246
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:49,480
The one you took is cursed!

247
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:52,110
It's quite scary.

248
00:20:52,110 --> 00:20:53,940
I do not wish to carry it!

249
00:20:53,940 --> 00:20:56,490
You'll be cursed!

250
00:21:02,740 --> 00:21:05,120
I'm leaving now, Grandpa Nose!

251
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:13,540
I won't forgive you
if anything happens to Otama!

252
00:21:13,540 --> 00:21:15,380
Yeah, I'll save her at any cost!

253
00:21:15,840 --> 00:21:18,170
And don't forget to return the sword!

254
00:21:19,380 --> 00:21:20,800
Answer me!

255
00:21:22,090 --> 00:21:25,260
Why aren't you responding?!

256
00:21:36,940 --> 00:21:38,570
Oh, it's the dog!

257
00:21:38,570 --> 00:21:40,110
Will you carry us, boy?

258
00:21:47,490 --> 00:21:49,660
This is much easier!

259
00:21:49,660 --> 00:21:51,290
Take us straight to town!

260
00:21:59,670 --> 00:22:01,170
Wha...?! What?!

261
00:22:01,170 --> 00:22:02,220
Huh?

262
00:22:02,220 --> 00:22:04,550
Oh, Tama! You're up!

263
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:07,560
Big Bro, where are we going on Komachiyo?

264
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:08,720
To the doctor.

265
00:22:09,060 --> 00:22:11,560
Does this dog know the way?

266
00:22:18,190 --> 00:22:19,650
Ace is dead.

267
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:33,540
Whoa-whoa, stop! You're gonna fall!

268
00:22:36,000 --> 00:22:39,170
Big Bro, you're a liar!

269
00:22:44,260 --> 00:22:45,840
Ace can't come back!

270
00:22:46,930 --> 00:22:50,430
Everyone knows what happened
during the Summit War.

271
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:02,900
But...

272
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:06,820
he promised me...

273
00:23:07,490 --> 00:23:10,410
Ace will come back!

274
00:23:16,750 --> 00:23:17,880
Ace!

275
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:20,210
Take me to the sea with you!

276
00:23:21,840 --> 00:23:23,670
I'm old enough!

277
00:23:26,890 --> 00:23:29,510
But you're only five.

278
00:23:29,510 --> 00:23:31,470
I'm already five!

279
00:23:31,470 --> 00:23:33,390
Oh, you know what you're doing there.

280
00:23:33,390 --> 00:23:34,770
Sure do.

281
00:23:34,770 --> 00:23:37,520
You're gonna leave here soon, right?

282
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:40,230
Yeah! I have to finish this before then...

283
00:23:42,820 --> 00:23:44,110
I...

284
00:23:44,110 --> 00:23:49,200
don't wanna say goodbye to...
you and everyone else...

285
00:23:50,450 --> 00:23:51,620
Tama...

286
00:23:53,830 --> 00:23:55,710
We'll come back!

287
00:23:55,710 --> 00:23:57,920
After we become even greater pirates!

288
00:23:59,330 --> 00:24:04,090
Then, will you let me join your crew?

289
00:24:04,710 --> 00:24:07,880
I wanna go on adventures with you!

290
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:12,850
To be a pirate, you must be strong!

291
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,310
When I come back...

292
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:19,730
if you've become something like
a bewitching kunoichi, I'll take you along.

293
00:24:22,230 --> 00:24:25,610
Ace! Does she really need to be "bewitching"?!

294
00:24:28,950 --> 00:24:30,120
Ace!

295
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:30,990
– Huh?
– Huh?

296
00:24:31,370 --> 00:24:33,330
I got it!

297
00:24:33,330 --> 00:24:35,370
That's a promise, okay?!

298
00:24:42,670 --> 00:24:46,130
We were very close...

299
00:24:47,220 --> 00:24:51,510
He said he'd come back...

300
00:24:51,510 --> 00:24:54,810
Big Bro, you don't know how nice he is!

301
00:24:55,180 --> 00:24:58,560
That's why you don't understand my pain!

302
00:24:58,560 --> 00:25:02,270
It doesn't hurt, but stop hitting me...

303
00:25:02,270 --> 00:25:05,530
How could talk so casually about him dying?!

304
00:25:08,820 --> 00:25:12,870
You're a dummy, Big Bro!

305
00:25:18,460 --> 00:25:21,500
Oh! We're almost out of the bamboo forest!

306
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:35,100
Grandpa Nose was right...

307
00:25:35,470 --> 00:25:37,720
It really is a wilderness!

308
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:50,320
It's a tiger!

309
00:25:52,910 --> 00:25:54,120
And a boar!

310
00:25:57,910 --> 00:25:59,200
What is that?!

311
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:01,290
Th-That's a Sharkodile!

312
00:26:01,290 --> 00:26:03,370
Talk about wild!

313
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:08,380
Just eat them if you're ever hungry!

314
00:26:08,710 --> 00:26:10,720
We can't...

315
00:26:10,720 --> 00:26:18,010
All the samurai who used to hunt them
have either been arrested or become bandits...

316
00:26:18,770 --> 00:26:20,230
Besides...

317
00:26:24,310 --> 00:26:27,400
Animals drink the polluted river water, too...

318
00:26:27,980 --> 00:26:32,320
so people get poisoned if they eat them.

319
00:26:32,780 --> 00:26:35,660
But they look so delicious!

320
00:26:35,660 --> 00:26:37,240
How could they?!

321
00:26:38,490 --> 00:26:40,700
Is that smoke from the factory?

322
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:42,290
Yes!

323
00:26:42,290 --> 00:26:46,420
They have a mine and a weapons factory...

324
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:51,050
so a lot of Kaido's subordinates are there.

325
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:55,140
What do they eat?

326
00:26:56,550 --> 00:27:01,020
The shogun and Kaido have...
an untainted farm...

327
00:27:01,350 --> 00:27:04,560
just for themselves.

328
00:27:06,310 --> 00:27:11,730
That's why they have clean water and rice...

329
00:27:12,190 --> 00:27:13,190
and fish...

330
00:27:16,110 --> 00:27:19,450
and lots... of meat...

331
00:27:19,870 --> 00:27:23,120
Man! So it's not like
there isn't any on this island!

332
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:27,670
Hey! Tama! Are you all right?!

333
00:27:28,290 --> 00:27:29,210
Ouch!

334
00:27:29,750 --> 00:27:31,840
I think you're getting warmer!

335
00:27:35,260 --> 00:27:36,630
Hang on!

336
00:27:38,340 --> 00:27:40,350
I'll get you to a doctor soon!

337
00:27:42,350 --> 00:27:46,310
If the enemy has food and water,
that's good enough for me!

338
00:27:46,310 --> 00:27:48,150
Hurry up, boy!

339
00:27:55,110 --> 00:27:57,240
Please forgive me!

340
00:28:00,530 --> 00:28:02,370
Wait, woman!

341
00:28:02,370 --> 00:28:05,120
Drop everything you have!

342
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:07,790
Help! Somebody!

343
00:28:26,350 --> 00:28:28,810
Damn! I'll make you pay for this!

344
00:28:29,980 --> 00:28:32,610
Step back, lady...

345
00:28:39,700 --> 00:28:43,120
"Zorojuro, Wanted for Murdering a Magistrate"

346
00:28:40,740 --> 00:28:44,370
You're that fugitive, Zorojuro!

347
00:28:45,120 --> 00:28:46,080
You fools.

348
00:28:46,870 --> 00:28:48,410
You have sake...

349
00:28:49,870 --> 00:28:50,830
Hand it over!

350
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:33,630
Sir Samurai!

351
00:29:39,510 --> 00:29:45,680
I don't know who you are,
but thank you for saving my life!

352
00:29:50,810 --> 00:29:53,060
Oh, don't mention it.

353
00:29:53,060 --> 00:29:56,570
I wanted their sake anyway... uh...

354
00:29:57,190 --> 00:29:58,570
verily.

355
00:29:58,570 --> 00:30:00,780
But I want to return the favor.

356
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:04,530
Then, more sake!

357
00:30:04,530 --> 00:30:06,990
Oh, I don't have any.

358
00:30:19,130 --> 00:30:20,470
That's Zoro!

359
00:30:21,470 --> 00:30:23,840
Hey, Zoro!

360
00:30:23,840 --> 00:30:25,470
It's me, it's me!

361
00:30:25,470 --> 00:30:27,680
Hey!

362
00:30:29,390 --> 00:30:31,020
Luffy!

363
00:30:31,020 --> 00:30:32,850
You made it!

364
00:30:34,270 --> 00:30:35,940
It's good to finally see you!

365
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:39,360
Zoro!

366
00:30:41,740 --> 00:30:43,860
Yahoo!

367
00:30:43,860 --> 00:30:45,160
Long time no see...

368
00:30:47,580 --> 00:30:49,700
Long time no see, verily and stuff!

369
00:30:56,420 --> 00:30:57,750
Is everyone with you?

370
00:30:57,750 --> 00:31:00,380
Yeah, but we got separated...

371
00:31:00,380 --> 00:31:02,920
I'm sure they're okay though!

372
00:31:10,100 --> 00:31:11,930
You have meat!

373
00:31:11,930 --> 00:31:13,310
Gimme some!

374
00:31:13,770 --> 00:31:18,110
There are a bunch of fish
and animals to hunt here, Luffy!

375
00:31:19,690 --> 00:31:22,240
You'll never be short of food!

376
00:31:22,240 --> 00:31:24,030
No, be careful!

377
00:31:24,570 --> 00:31:27,620
The water around here is poisonous!

378
00:31:27,990 --> 00:31:31,620
So I heard the meat and fish
are poisonous, too!

379
00:31:31,620 --> 00:31:34,790
I see. That's why I have a stomachache.

380
00:31:43,710 --> 00:31:46,720
Anyway, Zoro, come with us!

381
00:31:46,720 --> 00:31:51,720
A lot has happened, and I'm
on my way to take her to a doctor.

382
00:31:53,890 --> 00:31:55,730
A sick kid!

383
00:31:57,310 --> 00:31:59,270
You shouldn't be stopping to eat!

384
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:01,690
Don't worry!

385
00:32:01,690 --> 00:32:02,940
I'll eat fast!

386
00:32:08,740 --> 00:32:10,160
Just eat already!

387
00:32:10,160 --> 00:32:11,080
Okay!

388
00:32:21,210 --> 00:32:23,210
Are you...

389
00:32:24,260 --> 00:32:29,800
the ronin who is wanted
across the country, Zorojuro,

390
00:32:30,260 --> 00:32:32,140
and members of his clan?

391
00:32:38,310 --> 00:32:39,440
Oh?! He's...

392
00:32:39,980 --> 00:32:41,190
That's right...

393
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:44,440
Seems like he works for Kaido now.

394
00:32:47,450 --> 00:32:49,280
Straw Hat!

395
00:32:50,620 --> 00:32:54,240
I was on my way to Kuri Beach...

396
00:32:54,620 --> 00:32:57,460
but you caused the ruckus there, didn't you?

397
00:32:58,830 --> 00:33:01,880
Two of my subordinates
and one baboon went missing...

398
00:33:05,050 --> 00:33:05,090
Basil Hawkins
One of the Beast Pirates' Headliners

399
00:33:05,090 --> 00:33:05,130
Basil Hawkins
One of the Beast Pirates' Headliners

400
00:33:05,130 --> 00:33:05,170
Basil Hawkins
One of the Beast Pirates' Headliners

401
00:33:05,170 --> 00:33:10,550
Basil Hawkins
One of the Beast Pirates' Headliners

402
00:33:08,590 --> 00:33:11,470
The possibility that you guys have
something to do with it...

403
00:33:11,470 --> 00:33:13,550
is 98 percent.

404
00:33:14,810 --> 00:33:16,350
But...

405
00:33:16,930 --> 00:33:18,890
that doesn't matter.

406
00:33:20,650 --> 00:33:26,610
In Wano, you either follow the strong
or become their prey...

407
00:33:34,080 --> 00:33:36,950
Luffy, Kin'emon told us...

408
00:33:37,950 --> 00:33:40,330
not to cause a disturbance.

409
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:50,380
Well, then I'll just have to...

410
00:33:51,010 --> 00:33:53,010
apologize to him later!
